# Tech Stack

Searchable Docs uses the following technologies:

## Frontend
- **Nuxt.js 3**: Vue-based framework ([nuxt.config.ts](mdc:nuxt.config.ts))
- **Vue.js 3**: Progressive JavaScript framework
- **TailwindCSS**: Utility-first CSS framework

## Backend
- **Nuxt.js Server API**: API routes in [server/api/](mdc:server/api)
- **Node.js**: JavaScript runtime

## Database
- **SQLite**: Via libsql/client ([server/db/client.ts](mdc:server/db/client.ts))
- **Drizzle ORM**: SQL toolkit and ORM ([drizzle.config.ts](mdc:drizzle.config.ts))

## Search & Processing
- **BullMQ/Redis**: Job queue processing ([server/services/job-queue.ts](mdc:server/services/job-queue.ts))
- **Ollama**: Local embedding model ([server/services/ollama.ts](mdc:server/services/ollama.ts))
- **Octokit**: GitHub API integration
- **Vector Search**: Semantic search with embeddings ([server/services/embedding.ts](mdc:server/services/embedding.ts))
